title: Inline Editor

!! Introduction

The Inline Editor is an optional floating popup that allows direct wikitext editing of the source text for any element. It must be enabled via [[Configuration]] before it appears in the [[Context Menu]].

!! Enabling

Set `$:/config/wikilabs/SourcePositionTracking/ShowEditInline` to `show` to add the "Edit inline" option to the context menu.

!! How to Use

# ''Right-click'' on any element with source position tracking
# Select ''Edit inline'' from the context menu
# The popup opens with the source wikitext pre-selected in a monospace textarea
# Edit the text as needed
# Press ''Apply'' (or ''Ctrl+Enter'') to splice the changes back into the source tiddler
# Press ''Cancel'' (or ''Escape'') to dismiss without changes

!! Panel Layout

* ''Header bar'' — draggable, shows the source position
* ''Textarea'' — monospace editor with the source wikitext, auto-focused on open
* ''Buttons'' — Apply and Cancel
* ''Resize handle'' — bottom-right corner for resizing

!! How It Works

The editor uses the exact character positions stored in `data-source-start` and `data-source-end` to extract and splice text. When you click Apply, the edited text replaces the original character range in the source tiddler's text field.

!! Layout Persistence

Panel size is stored in `$:/temp/sourcepos/editor-layout` and persists across popup reopens during the same session.

!! Positioning

* The popup appears ''below'' the clicked element by default
* Falls back to ''above'' the element if there is insufficient space below

!! Keyboard Shortcuts

|! Key |! Action |
| ''Ctrl+Enter'' |Apply changes |
| ''Escape'' |Cancel and close |

